The chocolate tart is a simple dessert that is a chocolate rich and creamy All you need is a premade cookie crust, that you can bake and while it’s cooling in the fridge overnight, you can make the filling. Ingredients For the crust: For the chocolate filling: Preparation Step 1 To make the crust, crush the whole Oreo cookies in a food processor, add melted butter and blend until it’s all moistened. Step 2 Using a lightly greased pan, press the crumb mixture on the sides of the pan. Step 3 Place in the freezer overnight. Step 4 To make the chocolate filling, using a heat-proof bowl, melt the chocolate and set it aside. Then using a separate pan, bring the heavy cream and butter to a low boil. Step 5 Remove from the heat and pour the mixture over the bittersweet chocolate. Step 6 Let stand for 1 minute and slowly stir together with a spatula until the chocolate is completely melted and smooth Step 7 Pour mixture over chilled crust and refrigerate until set, at least 2 hours or overnight Serve chilled, and enjoy with friends and family